<plot>Merry Widow is the story of a fragile young obituary writer, who suffers from an addiction to mourning the loss of her husband. Her obsessive rituals and cowering demeanor meet with cheeky criticism from her glib coworkers, when she returns from random funerals everyday on her lunch hour. At one of these funerals she meets a reclusive grounds keeper who gives her clarity into her own pathos and self-destruction. The question is -will she face the realization that holding on to her husband's memory also means holding onto a lifetime of grief and inadequacy?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?366591</url></doc>
